      "body" : "Minor edge case: a non-fatal error in FlushState (currently only low disk space) would override a MODE_INVALID, preventing misbehavior accounting and reject messages for the current tx. Since MODE_ERROR from FlushState is ignored in this case anyway, I think it'd be more robust to give FlushState a dummy CValidationState.",
